                            <comment id="14545237" author="JIRAUSER20603" created="Tue, 13 Dec 2022 20:43:54 -0800"  >Yes, we can use the suppression list. The downside is its harder to maintain and can accidentally silence other memory leaks since it matches function signatures.</comment>
                            <comment id="14545226" author="dholmes" created="Tue, 13 Dec 2022 15:38:31 -0800"  >I _really_ do not like seeing source code changes to provide tool support like this. Can we not use a suppression file for the &amp;quot;known leaks&amp;quot;?</comment>
                            <comment id="14544105" author="JIRAUSER20603" created="Thu, 8 Dec 2022 22:25:59 -0800"  >For clarification, this will only be used for development purposes. It will also catch leaks for native memory allocated by Java using ByteBuffer or MemorySegment. This could be useful for users, but doing so would require some LSan changes to produce meaningful stack traces for Java code. Currently all Java frames result in an `unknown module` entry.</comment>
